attributes.Long form description: The student is assembling a shelf. They screw the brackets onto the base, then screw on the bottom tray. They continue adding trays and screws until the final, top tray is in place. The student then adds wheels to the base of the shelf and tightens them.

attributes.Transcription: Hello and thank you for agreeing to the part in our study.
In front of you, you will see the parts to assemble for IKEA.
Your task for now will be to please assemble it.
You may now begin.

attributes.Action sentence: The student assembles the shelf's brackets.

attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: The student should rotate the leg

attributes.Transcription: Please flip the piece in your right hand.

attributes.Action Correctness: Wrong Action, corrected by instructor verbally
attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: The student connects the bar from the wrong side.

attributes.Transcription: Please flip it except the metal bar, it's based on the other side

attributes.Action sentence: The student assembles the brackets to the base of the shelf.

attributes.Transcription: Please puts the two bottom pieces together.
*unintelligible*
*unintelligible*

attributes.Action sentence: The student assembles the bottom tray of the shelf.

attributes.Transcription: Please put the bottom shelf in the base.

attributes.Action sentence: The student screws the right brackets onto the base of the shelf.
The student assembles the remaining trays on the base.

attributes.Transcription: Please lay the cabinet flaps on the table and put the two shelves inside the cabinet as it as possible.

Please screw the top shelf to the top of it.

I mean right I can see a small wrench.

attributes.Transcription: Make sure both your hands are visible by the camera.

attributes.Transcription: Please make the shelf cabinet flat on the table.
Please use both wrenches to tighten the wheels.

Thank you very much.
